          <text><![CDATA[<p> <b>Practice of Law Technical Clarification Act of 2017</b> </p> <p>This bill amends the Fair Debt Collection Practices Act to exclude from the definition of &quot;debt collector&quot; any law firm or licensed attorney: (1) serving, filing, or conveying formal legal pleadings, discovery requests, or other documents pursuant to the applicable rules of civil procedure; or (2) communicating in connection with a legal action to collect a debt on behalf of a client in, or at the direction of, a court of law or in the enforcement of a judgment. </p> <UL><UL> </UL> </UL> <BR>]]></text>
